1.0.1 (2026-07-12)
https://github.com/hipstereclipse/RobCo-Weather-MkV
- Fix the app hanging on the launch screen (dead controls, reboot required).
  v1.0.0 shipped a non-invoked closure returning {id, remove, ...} - the
  Pip-Boy 3000's loader contract. The Mk V firmware runs USER/*.js as a plain
  top-to-bottom script and never invokes such a closure, so the app never
  drew or registered inputs. The app now executes at load like the official
  Wand Company apps: submenu-takeover preamble, invoked closure, teardown
  registered on the Pip.remove / Pip.removeSubmenu hooks (fired on mode-dial
  navigate-away).
- Render directly to g in the device theme color (g.theme.fg) instead of the
  h / bC / g resolver; h does not exist on the Mk V and un-flipped bC drawing
  is never shown. Layout, views, controls, and data format are unchanged.
- Ensure knob handler exclusivity with Pip.removeAllListeners("knob1"/"knob2")
  before attaching, per the official inputs documentation. Torch keeps its
  stock flashlight behavior.
- Ship WEATHER.min.js as plain terser output; drop the Espruino-CLI
  pretokenise pass (no shipping Mk V app is pretokenised, and a parse failure
  presents as a silent hang).
- Rename package.json to metadata.json and align fields with the pip-boy.com
  registry schema (adds tags, storageOptional).

1.0.0 (2026-07-11)
https://github.com/hipstereclipse/RobCo-Weather-MkV
- Port RobCo Weather from the Pip-Boy 3000 (hipstereclipse/Robco-Weather) to
  the Pip-Boy 3000 Mk V. Features, views, strings, data format, and the
  companion's fetch logic are unchanged.
- App ships as USER/WEATHER.js (Form A closure, unchanged shape); all content
  re-flowed into the Mk V visible window x in [38, 438] on the 480x320 surface.
- Graphics resolved through the h / bC / g resolver so the app runs under the
  loader and against the raw firmware buffers.
- Pip.playSound("SCROLL"/"TAB") is now feature-detected with a
  Pip.knob1Click/Pip.knob2Click fallback; remove() additionally calls
  Pip.audioStop().
- Metadata moved from APPINFO/WEATHER.info to package.json (registry) plus an
  optional on-card APPINFO/weather.json friendly name.
- 1-bpp holotape icon APPINFO/WEATHER.IMG replaced by a PNG registry icon
  (assets/icon.png); make_icon.py now emits the PNG.
- Narrower window trims some cut() limits: ATMOS condition 18->15, detail
  strips 36->31, aurora Kp-slot label 24->15.
